--> push()
    --> add item to end of array
--> querySelector()
    --> select items in DOM based on element type, class, id
--> setAttribute()
    --> sets attribute (param 1) to value (param 2)
--> getAttribute()
    --> retrieves value specified attribute
--> createElement()
    --> creates element with specified tag
--> appendChild()
    --> self-explanatory :)
--> Math.random()
    --> random float between 0 and .999...
--> sort()
    -->
--> For loops



index.html
--> Basic Boilerplate
--> h3: displays current score / victory message
--> span w/ id="result": target in app.js for dynamic text
--> div class="grid": space designated for board

app.js
--> all content enclosed in addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {//all content here//}
--> const cardArray
    --> includes name / img
    --> contained in app.js to facilitate randomization / access
--> other const
    --> cardsChosen [] ; store name of clicked image
    --> cardsChosenID [] ; store ID of clicked image
    --> cardsWon [] ; store names of successfully matched cards
--> function createBoard()
    --> loop over cardArray
    --> create image element [var card =]
    --> set image attribute source to blank at outset
    --> set data-ID as i (facilitates access)
    --> on click, trigger flipCard
    --> append card to grid with appendChild
    --> call function to create board
--> function flipCard()
    --> create cardID variable and set it to the ID of the clicked card
        --> this.getAttribute('data-ID')
    --> push clicked card's name into cardsChosen array
    --> push cardID to cardsChosenID
    --> set source of image to the image associated with the cardID
    --> once two cards have been clicked, checkForMatch after 500 milliseconds
        --> setTimeout(function, time)
--> function checkForMatch() 
    --> new var / const  
        --> var cards: collection of cards available
        --> const optionOneID: ID of first card clicked
        --> const optionTwoID: ID of second card clicked
        --> resultDisplay: jQuery select #result
    --> if card names match 
        --> set img source to white
        --> add name of img to cardsWon
        --> success alert
    --> if card names do not match
        --> set img back to blank
        --> failure alert
    --> regardless of result
        --> clear cardsChosen array
        --> clear cardsChosenID array
        --> change textContent of resultDisplay to length of cardsWon array
        --> if length of cardsWon contains all of the names of the pictures in cardArray
            -->change textContent of resultDisplay to congratulations message

